#: templates/about.html:3 templates/base.html:93
msgid "About"
msgstr "Perihal"

#: templates/about.html:50
msgid "What is PleaseFix?"
msgstr "Apakah PleaseFix?"

#: templates/about.html:52
msgid ""
"A public, community-owned issue tracker for\n"
"    Malaysia. Official complaint channels close tickets; communities fix\n"
"    problems. PleaseFix keeps every issue open — and public — until it is\n"
"    actually fixed."
msgstr ""
"Penjejak isu awam milik komuniti untuk Malaysia. Saluran aduan rasmi menutup "
"tiket; komuniti menyelesaikan masalah. PleaseFix memastikan setiap isu kekal "
"terbuka — dan terbuka kepada umum — sehingga ia benar-benar selesai."

#: templates/about.html:58
msgid "See the difference: one real kind of issue"
msgstr "Lihat perbezaannya: satu contoh isu sebenar"

#: templates/about.html:60
msgid ""
"\"I cannot cross the road from the LRT station\n"
"    because of a barrier.\""
msgstr ""
"\"Saya tidak dapat melintas jalan dari stesen LRT kerana ada penghadang.\""

#: templates/about.html:64
msgid ""
"Watch how the same complaint plays out in an\n"
"    official system and in PleaseFix."
msgstr ""
"Lihat bagaimana aduan yang sama berjalan dalam sistem rasmi dan dalam "
"PleaseFix."

#: templates/about.html:70
msgid "Back"
msgstr "Undur"

#: templates/about.html:71
msgid "Next day"
msgstr "Hari seterusnya"

#: templates/about.html:76
msgid "Official channel"
msgstr "Saluran rasmi"

#: templates/about.html:77 templates/about.html:94
msgid "Day 1"
msgstr "Hari 1"

#: templates/about.html:78
msgid "Complaint filed with the local council."
msgstr "Aduan difailkan kepada pihak berkuasa tempatan."

#: templates/about.html:79 templates/about.html:82 templates/about.html:102
msgid "Day 14"
msgstr "Hari 14"

#: templates/about.html:80
msgid "Council:"
msgstr "PBT:"

#: templates/about.html:81
msgid "\"Not our jurisdiction — that land belongs to the rail operator.\""
msgstr "\"Bukan bidang kuasa kami — tanah itu milik pengendali rel.\""

#: templates/about.html:83
msgid "Ticket closed. Case resolved — on paper."
msgstr "Tiket ditutup. Kes selesai — di atas kertas."

#: templates/about.html:84
msgid "Day 15+"
msgstr "Hari 15+"

#: templates/about.html:85
msgid ""
"The barrier is still there. Starting over means a new\n"
"          complaint, to a different agency, from zero — and the history of "
"the\n"
"          first one is invisible to everyone else."
msgstr ""
"Penghadang masih di situ. Untuk memulakan semula, aduan baharu perlu "
"difailkan kepada agensi lain, dari kosong — dan sejarah aduan pertama tidak "
"kelihatan kepada sesiapa pun."

#: templates/about.html:89
msgid "(nothing further happens)"
msgstr "(tiada apa-apa lagi berlaku)"

#: templates/about.html:95
msgid ""
"Issue opened — public from the first minute, pinned\n"
"          to the map, with photos. Neighbours subscribe and add their own\n"
"          evidence."
msgstr ""
"Isu dibuka — terbuka kepada umum dari minit pertama, ditanda pada peta, "
"dengan gambar. Jiran-jiran melanggan dan menambah bukti mereka sendiri."

#: templates/about.html:98
msgid "Day 2"
msgstr "Hari 2"

#: templates/about.html:99
msgid ""
"Filings fan out and are tracked on the issue:\n"
"          SISPAA (rejected), council (filed), rail operator (filed), local\n"
"          councillor (raised). Each gets its official reference number."
msgstr ""
"Failan dihantar serentak dan dijejak pada isu: SISPAA (ditolak), PBT "
"(difailkan), pengendali rel (difailkan), ahli majlis tempatan "
"(dibangkitkan). Setiap satu mendapat nombor rujukan rasminya."

#: templates/about.html:103
msgid ""
"The council closes their ticket — that closes\n"
"          <strong>their filing</strong>, not the issue. The issue stays "
"open,\n"
"          with the rejection on the record."
msgstr ""
"PBT menutup tiket mereka — itu menutup <strong>failan mereka</strong>, bukan "
"isu ini. Isu kekal terbuka, dengan penolakan itu tercatat dalam rekod."

#: templates/about.html:106
msgid "Day 30"
msgstr "Hari 30"

#: templates/about.html:107
msgid ""
"The councillor raises it with the rail operator,\n"
"          pointing at the public record: dated photos, four filings, one "
"open\n"
"          issue everyone can see."
msgstr ""
"Ahli majlis membangkitkannya dengan pengendali rel, sambil menunjukkan rekod "
"awam: gambar bertarikh, empat failan, satu isu terbuka yang boleh dilihat "
"semua."

#: templates/about.html:110
msgid "Day 60"
msgstr "Hari 60"

#: templates/about.html:111
msgid ""
"The operator commits to a crossing. Status updates\n"
"          land on the issue; subscribers are notified."
msgstr ""
"Pengendali komited untuk membina lintasan. Kemas kini status direkodkan pada "
"isu; pelanggan dimaklumkan."

#: templates/about.html:113
msgid "Day 90"
msgstr "Hari 90"

#: templates/about.html:114
msgid ""
"The crossing is built. The community confirms with\n"
"          photos — and only then is the issue closed: <strong>fixed, "
"verified by\n"
"          the people who reported it</strong>."
msgstr ""
"Lintasan siap dibina. Komuniti mengesahkannya dengan gambar — dan barulah "
"isu ditutup: <strong>selesai, disahkan oleh mereka yang melaporkannya</"
"strong>."

#: templates/about.html:121
msgid "Issues can be goals — try it"
msgstr "Isu boleh jadi matlamat — cuba sendiri"

#: templates/about.html:123
msgid ""
"Citizens have goals, not category codes. No\n"
"    government form can represent \"I want to walk safely from A to B\" —\n"
"    PleaseFix models it as an issue blocked by other issues, each possibly\n"
"    a different agency's problem. Resolve the blockers below:"
msgstr ""
"Rakyat ada matlamat, bukan kod kategori. Tiada borang kerajaan yang boleh "
"mewakili \"Saya mahu berjalan dengan selamat dari A ke B\" — PleaseFix "
"memodelkannya sebagai isu yang disekat oleh isu-isu lain, masing-masing "
"mungkin masalah agensi berbeza. Selesaikan penyekat di bawah:"

#: templates/about.html:130
msgid "\"I can't walk from the LRT to the school\" —"
msgstr "\"Saya tidak dapat berjalan dari LRT ke sekolah\" —"

#: templates/about.html:132 templates/about.html:134
msgid "blocked"
msgstr "disekat"

#: templates/about.html:133
msgid "partially unblocked"
msgstr "sebahagian terbuka"

#: templates/about.html:134
msgid "ready to verify & close"
msgstr "sedia disahkan & ditutup"

#: templates/about.html:137
msgid "No pedestrian crossing at the junction"
msgstr "Tiada lintasan pejalan kaki di simpang"

#: templates/about.html:138 templates/about.html:144
msgid "council"
msgstr "PBT"

#: templates/about.html:140
msgid "Streetlights out along the walkway"
msgstr "Lampu jalan terpadam di sepanjang laluan"

#: templates/about.html:141
msgid "utility"
msgstr "utiliti"

#: templates/about.html:143
msgid "Broken drain cover on the path"
msgstr "Penutup longkang pecah di laluan"

#: templates/about.html:145
msgid ""
"(Interactive with JavaScript: checking\n"
"      all blockers marks the main issue ready to close.)"
msgstr ""
"(Interaktif dengan JavaScript: menanda semua penyekat menjadikan isu utama "
"sedia untuk ditutup.)"

#: templates/about.html:149
msgid "What makes PleaseFix different"
msgstr "Apa yang membezakan PleaseFix"

#: templates/about.html:152
msgid "Public by default — issues belong to everyone they affect"
msgstr "Terbuka secara lalai — isu milik semua yang terkesan"

#: templates/about.html:153
msgid ""
"An official complaint is a private conversation\n"
"    between one person and one agency. A PleaseFix issue is a shared\n"
"    community record: anyone can see it, add photos and updates, subscribe,\n"
"    or follow up on an issue an agency already \"closed\". Duplicate\n"
"    reporters become subscribers instead of noise."
msgstr ""
"Aduan rasmi ialah perbualan peribadi antara seorang pengadu dan satu agensi. "
"Isu PleaseFix ialah rekod komuniti yang dikongsi: sesiapa sahaja boleh "
"melihatnya, menambah gambar dan kemas kini, melanggan, atau menyusul isu "
"yang telah \"ditutup\" oleh agensi. Pelapor pendua menjadi pelanggan, bukan "
"gangguan."

#: templates/about.html:161
msgid "Evidence that can't be quietly closed"
msgstr "Bukti yang tidak boleh ditutup senyap-senyap"

#: templates/about.html:162
msgid ""
"It has happened that a council closed tickets as\n"
"    \"done\" when the contractor had done nothing. On PleaseFix the trail "
"is\n"
"    public and permanent: dated photos, the date each complaint was lodged\n"
"    and with whom, every status change. The record outlives the agency's\n"
"    ticket — that is the point."
msgstr ""
"Pernah berlaku PBT menutup tiket sebagai \"selesai\" sedangkan kontraktor "
"tidak membuat apa-apa. Di PleaseFix, jejaknya terbuka dan kekal: gambar "
"bertarikh, tarikh setiap aduan difailkan dan kepada siapa, setiap perubahan "
"status. Rekod ini kekal melangkaui tiket agensi — itulah tujuannya."

#: templates/about.html:170
msgid "Cross-jurisdictional by design"
msgstr "Merentas bidang kuasa secara reka bentuk"

#: templates/about.html:171
msgid ""
"Government systems are one-agency silos;\n"
"    coordinating them has historically taken joint task forces or entire\n"
"    new agencies. One broken streetlight on a federal road near a rail\n"
"    station can genuinely involve three bodies. PleaseFix tracks one issue\n"
"    across every responsible agency at once — each filing with its own\n"
"    official reference number and status."
msgstr ""
"Sistem kerajaan ialah silo satu agensi; untuk menyelaraskannya, pernah "
"sampai memerlukan pasukan petugas bersama atau agensi baharu sepenuhnya. "
"Satu lampu jalan rosak di jalan persekutuan berhampiran stesen rel boleh "
"benar-benar melibatkan tiga pihak. PleaseFix menjejak satu isu merentasi "
"setiap agensi yang bertanggungjawab serentak — setiap failan dengan nombor "
"rujukan rasmi dan statusnya sendiri."

#: templates/about.html:180
msgid "Community status ≠ official status"
msgstr "Status komuniti ≠ status rasmi"

#: templates/about.html:181
msgid ""
"Each agency filing carries that agency's status\n"
"    (filed, rejected, \"selesai\"). The issue's status belongs to the\n"
"    community: it closes when the problem is verifiably fixed, not when a\n"
"    ticket is. \"Agency says fixed, community says not\" is representable —\n"
"    and visible."
msgstr ""
"Setiap failan agensi membawa status agensi itu (difailkan, ditolak, "
"\"selesai\"). Status isu milik komuniti: ia ditutup apabila masalah terbukti "
"selesai, bukan apabila tiket ditutup. \"Agensi kata selesai, komuniti kata "
"belum\" boleh direkodkan — dan dilihat semua."

#: templates/about.html:189
msgid "Tags beyond government categories"
msgstr "Tag melangkaui kategori kerajaan"

#: templates/about.html:190
msgid ""
"Issues carry community tags no agency taxonomy\n"
"    supports — accessibility, CEDAW, public transport, environment — so\n"
"    advocates can see, for example, every accessibility issue in one\n"
"    neighbourhood at once."
msgstr ""
"Isu membawa tag komuniti yang tiada dalam taksonomi mana-mana agensi — "
"kebolehcapaian, CEDAW, pengangkutan awam, alam sekitar — supaya pendukung "
"boleh melihat, contohnya, semua isu kebolehcapaian di satu kejiranan "
"serentak."

#: templates/about.html:197
msgid "It teaches jurisdiction"
msgstr "Ia mengajar bidang kuasa"

#: templates/about.html:198
msgid ""
"Who is responsible for what is tribal knowledge.\n"
"    PleaseFix explains it — per issue type and per area — and records the\n"
"    official reference numbers, so the government-side trail is trackable\n"
"    from the public one and the next reporter files smarter."
msgstr ""
"Siapa bertanggungjawab atas apa selalunya menjadi pengetahuan lisan semata-"
"mata. PleaseFix menerangkannya — mengikut jenis isu dan kawasan — dan "
"merekodkan nombor rujukan rasmi, supaya jejak di pihak kerajaan boleh "
"disusuli daripada rekod awam dan pelapor seterusnya memfailkan dengan lebih "
"bijak."

#: templates/about.html:204
msgid "How it works"
msgstr "Cara ia berfungsi"

#: templates/about.html:207 templates/base.html:91
msgid "Report"
msgstr "Lapor"

#: templates/about.html:208
msgid "Route"
msgstr "Halakan"

#: templates/about.html:209
msgid "Dispatch"
msgstr "Hantar"

#: templates/about.html:210
msgid "Track"
msgstr "Jejak"

#: templates/about.html:211
msgid "Verify"
msgstr "Sahkan"

#: templates/about.html:213
msgid ""
"Report with a photo and a pin on the map (no\n"
"    account needed — a phone number or email is enough). PleaseFix works "
"out\n"
"    the responsible agencies from the location and category, dispatches to\n"
"    each of them, and records every filing. Updates flow back — by agency\n"
"    reply, by staff liaison, or by neighbours adding evidence — and the\n"
"    community verifies the fix before the issue closes."
msgstr ""
"Lapor dengan gambar dan pin pada peta (tiada akaun diperlukan — nombor "
"telefon atau e-mel sudah memadai). PleaseFix menentukan agensi yang "
"bertanggungjawab berdasarkan lokasi dan kategori, menghantar kepada setiap "
"satu, dan merekodkan setiap failan. Kemas kini mengalir kembali — melalui "
"balasan agensi, pegawai perhubungan, atau jiran yang menambah bukti — dan "
"komuniti mengesahkan pembaikan sebelum isu ditutup."

#: templates/about.html:221
msgid "Built to be built on"
msgstr "Dibina untuk dibina di atasnya"

#: templates/about.html:222
msgid ""
"PleaseFix is open source (Apache-2.0) and\n"
"  deliberately contributor-friendly: Django + HTMX, strict typing, one\n"
"  <code>docker compose up</code> for the whole stack. The public API is a\n"
"  first-class product — build your own reporting app, neighbourhood\n"
"  dashboard, or advocacy view on the same public data."
msgstr ""
"PleaseFix ialah sumber terbuka (Apache-2.0) dan sengaja dibina mesra "
"penyumbang: Django + HTMX, penaipan ketat, satu <code>docker compose up</"
"code> untuk keseluruhan sistem. API awam ialah produk kelas pertama — bina "
"aplikasi pelaporan, papan pemuka kejiranan, atau paparan advokasi anda "
"sendiri di atas data awam yang sama."

